Use : mount_gentoo.sh [OPTIONS]

--help (-h)
    This help message

SCENARIO 1 : Chrooting the gentoo environment. Before, you can mount the gentoo directories.

    OPTION
    --mount(-m)
        mouting the gentoo directories before chrooting

    MANDATORY
    --block(-b) BLOCK
        block device (format /dev/sdX) on which the gentoo directory is to be mounted

SCENARIO 2 : you're logged off the gentoo environment and you want to unmount the directories
 
   --umount(-u)
        unmounting the gentoo directories

